  "input": "A 12-year-old male patient presented with a subcutaneous nodule on the anterolateral surface of his right leg. The nodule, first noticed by the patient's family about a month prior, had been growing slowly. On physical examination, the nodule measured approximately 2 cm in diameter, had a well-defined border, and was located within the skin and subcutaneous tissue. It exhibited a bluish discoloration but was not associated with pain or ulceration. An excisional procedure was performed under local anesthesia within a week of the initial presentation. The lesion was removed with 1 to 2 cm margins, including skin and subcutaneous tissue above the fascial plane. Written informed consent was obtained from the patient's legal guardians.",
  "target": "Dermatofibrosarcoma protuberans",
